<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Swap"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Swap"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange interest rate swaps.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Swap Trades</title>

    <para role="TEXT">Interest rate swaps allow two parties to exchange or "swap" a series
    of interest payments without exchanging the underlying debt. The least
    complicated interest rate swaps are commonly referred to as "plain vanilla
    swaps". They usually involve one party exchanging a portion of its
    interest payments on a floating rate debt for a portion of the interest
    payments on another party’s fixed rate debt.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When a deal is initiated, <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
    xpointer="ent_applisump" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    looks to the system setup default values for data necessary for trade
    pricing. You can also create and edit templates in a user-friendly
    interface.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">When you enter minimum information in the form of a maturity (tenor)
    date and notional amount, <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
    xpointer="ent_applisump" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    derives the remaining data for the index and currency. Under these
    circumstances, <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
    xpointer="ent_applisump" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
    defaults to a "plain vanilla swap" (pay fixed/receive float) using the
    default currency and index specifications.</para>
  </section>

